// Cluster 11 — NEW commercial food processor repair pillar.
// Same template family. $120 commercial diagnostic. Em-dash ≤2. NO C-38, NO C-20.
// BHGS #A49573 + EPA 608 #1346255700410.
//
// Brand factual: Robot Coupe (French, SEB Group) R-series cutter mixers,
// Hobart (ITW Food Equipment) buffalo choppers, Univex (independent),
// Vitamix Commercial (independent). Health Department sanitization angle.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import CommercialHero from '../../components/CommercialHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/commercial/food-processor-repair/";

const title = "Commercial Food Processor Repair LA | Robot Coupe R-Series, Hobart Buffalo Chopper, Univex";
const description = "Commercial food processor repair across SoCal. Robot Coupe R-series cutter mixers, Hobart buffalo choppers, Univex, Vitamix Commercial. $120 dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Do you service Robot Coupe, Hobart buffalo choppers, Univex, and Vitamix Commercial?",
    a: "Yes. Robot Coupe (French, SEB Group) R-series cutter mixers (R2, R4, R8, R10, R15, R30) are the dominant US market for commercial food processing and the bulk of our service volume. Hobart buffalo choppers (84142, 84186 series) are heritage units still in service in many LA-area delis and butcher shops. Univex (independent) covers the mid-tier countertop segment. Vitamix Commercial (independent) handles high-volume blender applications."
  },
  {
    q: "My Robot Coupe blade dulls quickly. Is that normal?",
    a: "Depends on usage. Daily processing of fibrous vegetables (celery, carrots, root vegetables) dulls blades faster than soft cheese or cooked items. Typical Robot Coupe S-blade service life is 6 to 18 months depending on usage; manufacturer recommendation is to sharpen at first sign of strain on the motor and replace when sharpening is no longer viable. We sharpen on-site or replace with OEM Robot Coupe blades; aftermarket blades often fail Health Department inspection regardless of fitment."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Health Department require for food processor sanitization?",
    a: "LA County Health Department requires daily sanitization (not just rinse cleaning) of food processors used for ready-to-eat foods. The blade, blade housing, lid, bowl, and base interface all require breakdown for proper sanitization. NSF-listed parts are required for ready-to-eat food contact surfaces; we install only NSF-listed OEM replacement parts so your processor remains Health Dept inspection-ready."
  },
  {
    q: "Why does my Robot Coupe motor stop mid-cycle?",
    a: "Three causes: (1) overload trip from over-filling the bowl (Robot Coupe motors have thermal protection that trips on extended overload; reset and reduce batch size), (2) safety interlock fault on the lid (lid must be properly seated for motor to run; year 5 to 9 typical interlock wear), (3) motor brushes worn out (Robot Coupe motors are brushed, year 6 to 10 typical brush life). We diagnose with multimeter and visual inspection. Brush replacement runs $260 to $440; full motor replacement $680 to $1,200."
  },
  {
    q: "Hobart buffalo chopper: still serviceable?",
    a: "Yes. Hobart 84142 and 84186 buffalo choppers are heritage units; many in LA service have been running since the 1980s with periodic component replacement. We service blade replacement, motor service, drive belt, safety interlock, and bowl bearing rebuild. Hobart parts via ITW authorized distribution; some vintage components require aftermarket cross-reference but most service items remain available."
  },
  {
    q: "What does commercial food processor repair cost in LA?",
    a: "$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. Common Robot Coupe repairs: blade sharpening or replacement (S-blade) $180 to $360, motor brush replacement $260 to $440, safety interlock replacement $260 to $440, motor replacement $680 to $1,200, bowl latch service $140 to $260, drive coupling $200 to $360. Common Hobart buffalo chopper repairs: blade replacement $480 to $820, motor service $880 to $1,400, drive belt $180 to $320, bowl bearing rebuild $580 to $880. Multi-component repair $890 to $1,800."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor warranty on every repair. Robot Coupe, Hobart, Univex, and Vitamix Commercial component warranties (where applicable) processed separately through manufacturer authorized networks. BHGS #A49573 and BBB A+. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410."
  }
];

