<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Food processor service</p>
    <h2>Commercial food processor service for restaurants, delis, prep kitchens, and butcher shops.</h2>

    <p>Commercial food processors handle prep volumes that residential processors can't. Restaurant prep lines, deli salad production, butcher shop sausage seasoning, ice cream base preparation, and ready-to-eat food assembly all depend on cutter mixer or buffalo chopper reliability. We service commercial food processors across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties.</p>

    <p><strong>Robot Coupe</strong> (French, SEB Group) R-series cutter mixers are the dominant US market: R2 (2.5 quart, smallest), R4 (4.5 quart), R8, R10, R15, R30 (30 quart, floor model). Robot Coupe is the bulk of our food processor service volume across LA-area restaurants and delis. <strong>Hobart buffalo choppers</strong> (ITW Food Equipment, 84142 and 84186 series) are heritage units still in service in many LA delis and butcher shops, some running since the 1980s with periodic component replacement. <strong>Univex</strong> (independent) covers mid-tier countertop. <strong>Vitamix Commercial</strong> (independent) handles high-volume blender applications.</p>

    <p>Service scope: blade sharpening and replacement (NSF-listed OEM only for Health Department compliance), motor brush service (Robot Coupe brushed motors), motor replacement, safety interlock service, bowl latch service, drive coupling, drive belt, bowl bearing rebuild on Hobart buffalo choppers. Heritage Hobart buffalo chopper service available; vintage components sometimes require aftermarket cross-reference but most service items remain available.</p>

    <p>$120 commercial diagnostic, waived with repair. BHGS #A49573 license. EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7. <a href="/credentials/licensed/">License verifiable.</a></p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Failure modes</p>
    <h2>Typical commercial food processor failures, in order of frequency.</h2>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Blade dulling.</strong> Routine maintenance. Robot Coupe S-blade service life 6 to 18 months depending on usage. Sharpening or replacement $180 to $360. Aftermarket blades often fail Health Department inspection.</li>
      <li><strong>Safety interlock failure.</strong> Year 5 to 9 typical. Lid must be properly seated for motor to run. Replacement $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor brush wear (Robot Coupe).</strong> Robot Coupe motors are brushed; year 6 to 10 typical brush life. Symptom: motor runs erratically, sparking visible at brush block. Replacement $260 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Bowl latch wear.</strong> Lid latches loose, lid won't seat properly, safety interlock prevents motor start. $140 to $260.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive coupling.</strong> The plastic or metal coupling between motor shaft and blade spindle wears or breaks. $200 to $360.</li>
      <li><strong>Motor overload trip.</strong> Operator over-filling the bowl. Reset, reduce batch size, educate operator. No-charge fix on first occurrence.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive belt (Hobart buffalo, Univex floor models).</strong> Year 4 to 7. $180 to $320.</li>
      <li><strong>Hobart buffalo bowl bearing.</strong> Year 12 to 20+ on heritage units. Rebuild $580 to $880.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 BRANDS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Brand notes</p>
    <h2>What we see by brand on food processor service calls.</h2>

    <p><strong>Robot Coupe (French, SEB Group).</strong> R-series cutter mixers: R2, R4, R8, R10, R15, R30. Brushed motor architecture, S-blade primary cutting tool, separate veggie-prep attachments on larger models. Robot Coupe parts via SEB Group US distribution; standard 5 to 7 day ship.</p>

    <p><strong>Hobart buffalo chopper (ITW Food Equipment).</strong> 84142, 84186 series. Heritage units. Cast-iron bowl bearings, large blade in horizontal axis, fed by rotating bowl. Heritage Hobart parts available through ITW authorized distribution; some vintage 1970s and 80s components require aftermarket cross-reference.</p>

    <p><strong>Univex (independent).</strong> Mid-tier countertop and floor food processors. Less expensive than Robot Coupe, simpler architecture. Common in mid-volume operations.</p>

    <p><strong>Vitamix Commercial (independent).</strong> High-volume commercial blenders for smoothie operations, soup pureeing, juice bars. Different architecture from cutter mixers; we service motor, drive coupling, container assembly.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 STORIES -->
