        <h3>Restaurant prep kitchen in West Hollywood · Robot Coupe R8 (8 years)</h3>
        <p>Motor running erratically with visible sparking. Diagnosed: motor brushes worn to base. Replaced brush set plus cleaned commutator. Tested through full prep cycle. Total: $360.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Deli in Beverly Hills · Hobart buffalo chopper 84186 (18 years)</h3>
        <p>Bowl rotation noisy plus blade dulling beyond viability. Rebuilt bowl bearings (vintage Hobart heritage service) plus replaced blade with NSF-listed OEM. Total: $1,420. Owner happy to keep the original cabinet running.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Salad operation in Pasadena · Robot Coupe R10 (5 years)</h3>
        <p>Lid wouldn't seat properly; safety interlock prevented start. Bowl latch wear. Replaced bowl latch plus tested interlock through full cycle. Total: $260.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Juice bar in Long Beach · Vitamix Commercial Vita-Prep 3 (4 years)</h3>
        <p>Motor stopping under load. Diagnosed: drive coupling worn (high-volume blender drive couplings wear faster than cutter mixer designs). Replaced coupling. Total: $280.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Butcher shop in Los Angeles · Hobart buffalo chopper 84142 (22 years)</h3>
        <p>Blade replacement plus drive belt cracking. Replaced both with OEM (Hobart parts available, no aftermarket cross-reference needed for these items). Tested through full chop cycle. Total: $940.</p>
      </div>
